text: An election happened on November 3, 2020 to elect a Senator from the U.S. state of Alaska. The two people in the election were Dan Sullivan (Republican Party), Al Gross (independent), and John Wayne Howe (Alaskan Independence Party), was also on the ballot and finished a distant third. Sullivan won the election and stayed as a Senator. Primary elections happened on August 18, 2020. Nobody ran against Sullivan in the Republican party. ==Republican Party primary== ==Libertarian-Democratic-Independence primary== ==Results== ==Notes== ==References== Category:2020 United States Senate elections Category:Alaska elections Category:2020s in Alaska
title: 2020 United States Senate election in Alaska
